	<string name="help_title">Help &amp; Feedback</string>
	<string name="help_intro">Translate HTML documents while keeping structure,
		tags,
		links, and code blocks as close to the original as possible.</string>
	<string name="help_usage_title">How to use the app</string>
	<string name="help_usage_body">1. Paste HTML, choose an example file, pick a
		local
		.html file, or load HTML from a URL.
		\n2. Download the required ML Kit
		language model if it is missing on
		your device.
		\n3. Select source
		language and target language.
		\n4. Tap Translate.
		\n5. Use Render
		preview HTML or side-by-side compare to review the
		result.
		\n6. Save or
		share the translated HTML.</string>
	<string name="help_html_support_title">What stays protected</string>
	<string name="help_html_support_body">• HTML tags and element structure stay
		intact.
		\n•
		Attributes, URL paths, and placeholders can be protected based on
		your
		options.
		\n• Code-like content inside protected areas is not
		translated.
		\n• Whitespace and line layout are preserved where
		possible.</string>
	<string name="help_translation_tips_title">Tips for better results</string>
	<string name="help_translation_tips_body">• Use valid HTML before translating.
		\n• Keep
		scripts, style blocks, and technical identifiers in protected
		sections.
		\n• Very large files can take longer to prepare and
		translate.
		\n• Review technical terms, product names, and
		mixed-language content
		before publishing.
		\n• If output looks unusual,
		fix HTML structure and translate again.</string>
	<string name="help_model_title">Language models</string>
	<string name="help_model_body">ML Kit translates on this device after the
		required
		language model is downloaded.
		The first translation for a target
		language may need internet access.
		Open Manage language models to
		download or delete models when you need
		offline access or more storage
		space.</string>
	<string name="help_troubleshooting_title">Troubleshooting</string>
	<string name="help_troubleshooting_body">• Translate button disabled: enter HTML
		and choose
		different source and target languages.
		\n• Model download fails: check
		internet connection and available
		storage.
		\n• Some content is not
		translated: protected tags, paths, URLs, and
		placeholders may be
		intentionally skipped.
		\n• Rendered preview looks wrong: check that the
		source HTML is valid.</string>
	<string name="help_developer_notes_title">For developers</string>
	<string name="help_developer_notes_body">This sample uses MlKitHtmlTranslator to
		prepare HTML
		nodes, translate human-readable chunks, and rebuild the
		document.
		Use
		explainHtml() to inspect chunks and protected nodes without
		performing
		translation.
		Close the translator when the owner is destroyed.</string>
